g.text: Training GBM Model for classification with H2O
This tutorial shows how to train an H2O Model in KNIME. We will train a Gradient Boosting Machine Model Classifier to predict the reponse class of the IRIS
Load the IRIS data, import the resulting KNIME Table to H2O, Preview its Statistics, partition the data for test and train set 25/75.
We learn the GBM Model using the H2O Gradient Boosting Machine Learner (Classification). We want H2O to build 100 Trees using a multinominal distribution of
the reponse, for it is a multilabel problem. All other model parameters are H2Os defaults.
Make predictions on new data using your model(s). In order to compute the Scoring metrics, we need to enable the "append individual class probabilities"
In order to evaluate our model, we asess the Classifiers accuracy by scoring the predictions made on the test data.
Export the Model using MOJO which can be used for deployment
